Lagos State Governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu, has appointed Oluremi Nurudeen Olaleye as the 11th Rector of the Lagos State Polytechnic (LASPOTECH). His new media aide, Gawat Jubril, made the announcement on Monday. Olaleye’s appointment was sequel to an interview conducted by the institution’s Governing Council and subsequent recommendation. The appointment is a 5 years single term and takes effect from December 1, 2020. The tenure of the Acting Rector, Olumide Olusola Metilelu, expires on the same day. Olaleye is currently the Chief Lecturer, Microbiology Unit of the Biological Sciences Department. The PhD holder is an expert in water, sanitation and hygiene researches.